HEADWORD: Coadunate
<hw>Co*ad"u*nate</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>coadunatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>coadunare</ets> to unite. See
<er>Adunation</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>United at the base, as
contiguous lobes of a leaf.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coadunation</ent>⟦br⟧
